                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="266138" author="lixi_wc" created="Thu, 26 Mar 2020 01:48:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The reason for this is, T10pi checksums are not normal checksum types like crc32c or alder. So the performance calculations are done in a different (but similar and comparable) way in a different place. The performance will only be calculated and printed when being used for the first time. It would be nice to print the performance together with other algorithms.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another more cirtical thing is, if T10PI checksum performance is much slower than other algorithms, a warning message should be printed. That is especially important for Lustre client which might be forced to use T10PI checksum even the performance is bad. An warning message would at least let the administrator notice the performance penalty.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
